{"Pharmacokinetic studies": [], "Hydrophilic drugs": [], "Lipophilic drugs": []}

The active transport systems present in the BBB can also affect the distribution of drugs within the CNS [21, 23].

{"Active transport systems": []}

The efflux transporters, such as P-glycoprotein (P-gp) and multidrug resistance-associated proteins (MRPs), can actively transport drugs out of the brain, thereby reducing their accumulation [21, 23].

{"Efflux transporters": [], "P-glycoprotein": ["P-glycoprotein"], "Multidrug resistance-associated proteins": ["multidrug resistance-associated proteins"]}

