The human cytochrome P450 system is composed of at least 57 distinct genes, which are divided into 18 families and 44 subfamilies.

{"Human cytochrome P450 system": ["human cytochrome P450 system"]}

Cytochrome P450 3A4 (CYP3A4) is the most abundant and most important isoform in the human liver. It is responsible for the metabolism of approximately 50% of all drugs.

{"Cytochrome P450 3A4 (CYP3A4)": ["cytochrome P450 3A4 (CYP3A4)"]}

